{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3>L14 -Introduction to Blockchain and Bitcoin</h3>\n<h2>Module content</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Construction and structure of blockchains</li>\n<li>Distributed trust and consensus</li>\n<li>Proof of Work›Block content and transactions</li>\n<li>Examples of blockchains (e.g. Bitcoin and Ethereum)</li>\n<li>Smart contracts›Ecosystems and infrastructure</li>\n<li>Application areas.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Learning resources, I</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://bitcoinbook.cs.princeton.edu/\">Website for Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency Technologies</a></p>\n<h3>Free draft of the book</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://d28rh4a8wq0iu5.cloudfront.net/bitcointech/readings/princeton_bitcoin_book.pdf\">Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency Technologies, The book</a></p>\n<h2>Learning resources, II</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf\">The Bicoinwhitepaper</a> by Satoshi Nakamotocan</p>\n<h2>Learning resources, III (cursory)</h2>\n<h3><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoinbook/bitcoinbook\">Mastering Bitcoin</a></h3>\n<p>Mastering Bitcoin is a book for developers, although the first two chapters cover bitcoin at a level that is also approachable to non-programmers. Anyone with a basic understanding of technology can read the first two chapters to get a great understanding of bitcoin.</p>\n<p>This repository contains the complete <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoinbook/bitcoinbook/releases/tag/Edition1Print2\">first edition, second print</a>, published in December 2014, and the complete <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoinbook/bitcoinbook/releases/tag/second_edition_print2\">second edition, second print</a>, published in July 2017, as published by O’Reilly Media in paperback and ebook formats.</p>\n<h3>Free draft of the book</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoinbook/bitcoinbook/releases/tag/second_edition_print2\">Bitcoin book</a></p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Lecture Notes</h1>\n<p>A bitcoin amount is always associated with a bitcoin address. Think of the address as an account number. The address is a hash of a public key. <br>\nWhen we transfer (spend) bitcoin, it “moves” from one address to another. <br>\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/f1b03/key.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.76131687242799%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Private-Public-key\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/1b588/key.png\"\n        srcset=\"/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/dabf4/key.png 148w,\n/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/6888f/key.png 295w,\n/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/1b588/key.png 590w,\n/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/5ad62/key.png 885w,\n/expr-site/static/95e4f5695f9159b19918f1294690ffbe/f1b03/key.png 972w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nTo spend bitcoin, you have to provide the private key for the sender address to prove that you “own” this address. <br>\nThink of the private key as a password. <br>\nA key-pair is created, from a random number, according to the Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm (ECDSA). <br></p>\n<h2>Key creation</h2>\n<p>In Bitcoin, a private key is a 256-bit number <br>\nNearly every 256-bit number is a valid ECDSA private key <br>\n=> The number of keys is 2<sup>256</sup> ~ 10<sup>77</sup>~ number of atoms in the universe <br>\nSo if you create a truly random private key, there is ~ zero chance that someone else can guess or create the same key. Even with much computing power, it is really hard to brute force a guess of your key. (In practice, there are more private keys than addresses (2<sup>160</sup>), but still …)</p>\n<h2>Bitcoin Network</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/2aab9/bitcoinNet.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 87.78004073319757%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Bitcoin Network\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/1b588/bitcoinNet.png\"\n        srcset=\"/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/dabf4/bitcoinNet.png 148w,\n/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/6888f/bitcoinNet.png 295w,\n/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/1b588/bitcoinNet.png 590w,\n/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/5ad62/bitcoinNet.png 885w,\n/expr-site/static/2d298af38e4548479b6a5a11cb845b34/2aab9/bitcoinNet.png 982w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Bitcoin Network With a distributed ledger</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/0d330/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 87.39999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Bitcoin Network with ledger\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/1b588/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png\"\n        srcset=\"/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/dabf4/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png 148w,\n/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/6888f/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png 295w,\n/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/1b588/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png 590w,\n/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/5ad62/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png 885w,\n/expr-site/static/3e97be5128dbf2de27de1001d4825a31/0d330/bitcoinNetWithLedger.png 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Block Explorers</h2>\n<p>The data in the Bitcoin blockchain is publicly available <br>\nBut the format is not human understandable <br>\nThere are a lot of applications that shows / visualizes / gives read-access to the data in the blockchain <br>\nThese are called block explorers <br>\n<a href=\"https://live.blockcypher.com/\">Example</a></p>","excerpt":"L14 -Introduction to Blockchain and Bitcoin Module content Construction and structure of blockchains Distributed trust and consensus Proof…","frontmatter":{"date":"November 23, 2018","dateUnformatted":"2018-11-23","path":"/blockchain/blockchain","title":"Blockchain","tags":"blockchain","author":"Preben Haukebøe","ogDescription":"All about Blockchain"}}},"pageContext":{}}